pr_review_body:
@dpeng817 re: cross-dagster-version compatibility
I updated this PR to switch to another approach (which is even less elegant but easier to roll back). I view this approach of adding op_selection_data to ExternalPipeline a short-term hot fix which I'm not sure about its long term and we may eventually remove. So if we move forward that, even if this PR doesn't cause the compatibility issue, at the time we remove that short-term fix (i.e. removing op_selection_data from ExternalPipeline), it for sure would cause the cross-dagster-version issue.

So, the other direction here is to do the same as pipeline definition [1] -- thread in "parent job def" so ExternalPipeline can pass the right selection info: https://github.com/dagster-io/dagster/blob/master/python_modules/dagster/dagster/core/host_representation/external.py#L242

@kghost I think this can be useful. 👍 

One general thought: If we want to track OT stack restarts, how about adding this in OT core instead of CLI? It can be part of `Instance` class? We can have a public API `uint32_t otInstanceGetId(otInstance *aInstance);`

This way it will track this independent of whether CLI is used or not?

@CharlesAuguste Could you please fix some minor data types-related issues and compiler warnings?

Can `advanced` method be used in parallel mode and has no any other limitations? In other words, should the following code be updated?
https://github.com/microsoft/LightGBM/blob/aa18f844c3066e843d235ea0d35c708abb9e61ed/src/io/config.cpp#L335-L345

@jarrodmillman, I've found one item that appeared due to wrong parsing of the script. 

With #6556 merged on Jan 10, I compared the generated list to this [search query `is:pr is:closed merged:>2023-01-10`](https://github.com/scikit-image/scikit-image/pulls?q=is%3Apr+is%3Aclosed+merged%3A%3E2023-01-10) which returns 58 items. It seems like the list contains 60 items (without the one I suggest to remove). We'll probably find the discrepancy when we sort and check them manually.

I am happy to help with that tomorrow.

@karczex, thank you for the PR!

Is it enough for you to have `pkg-config` support for build from sources only? Are you interested in having it in prebuilt packages from [release](https://github.com/oneapi-src/oneTBB/releases) page (not sure how to dynamically get `prefix` value in this case)?

Overall comment: the PR covers only `tbb` library in release configuration, but we need to take into account other oneTBB libraries (tbbmalloc, tbbbind, etc), consider debug libraries that have `_debug` suffix (`-ltbb_debug`). Most likely we should implement a common macro to run it for each target.

@Irving-cl  this is a great enhancement. Thank you 👍 👍 

I added some suggestion below on having `ItemType` be a nested type defined by `IteratorType`. I also like the suggestion to include `mItem` in the `ItemPtrIterator`. Thoughts?

Thanks.

LGTM minus minor suggestions.

Although could you help me understand how this comment relates to the `plugins: {providers ..}` section added to the YAML files? Is the comment referring to something else?

```
			// LocalProviders are relative to the working directory when running tests, NOT relative to the
			// Pulumi.yaml. This is a bit odd, but makes it easier to construct the required paths in each
			// test.
```

The path _appears_ to be the relative path to the tests/testprovider directory relative to the Pulumi.yaml, but your comment says it's not?
